The paper deals with node overlap removal algorithms in graphs, which is a topic that falls under computer graphics and visualization. Therefore, cs.GR (Computer Graphics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of data structures and algorithms to solve the problem, which could place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of computer vision techniques to evaluate the algorithms, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the usability of the algorithms for visualization designers, which could place it under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
